        "exhibitionLabelText": {
            "en": {
                "purposes": [
                    "The Weight of Lightness"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "The Weight of Lightness",
                        "text": "Hidai Nankoku’s works since the 1950s followed the brushwork of conventional calligraphy yet rejected any use of characters. The depictions in Work 63–12, referring to the year and sequence of production,resemble radicals in ChineseorJapanese characters butdonotin fact match any. Hidai treated the paper with resin to reduce ink absorption and revealed the effects of the brush dragging on the surface, especiallyatthe pointsofpressure where a marbling effect of the ink becomes visible.The work bringstothe forefrontthe process of making marks and the presence of the calligrapher."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "zh-hant": {
                "purposes": [
                    "The Weight of Lightness"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "The Weight of Lightness",
                        "text": "自五十年代起，比田井南谷的作品遵循傳統書法的筆道，但不採用任何具體文字。以創作年份和序號命題的《作品 63–12》，看似漢字部首或日文，但卻不具任何意義。比田井南谷在紙上塗上樹脂，以減少其吸墨度，呈現拖筆在畫面上運行的墨跡。壓筆轉折之處，墨汁凝結的紋理尤其顯著。此作將墨跡形成的過程以及藝術家的筆勢活現眼前。"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    },
